article.headline: Wright St. 62, Youngstown St. 49
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- DaShaun Wood had 17 points and five steals to lead Wright State to a 62-49 victory Wednesday over Youngstown State. Todd Brown added 16 points, including 4-of-6 shooting on 3-pointers, and Jordan Pleiman had nine points and 11 rebounds in a balanced attack for the Raiders (13-8, 6-2 Horizon League). Quin Humphrey scored 22 points and Keston Roberts had 10 for the Penguins (9-12, 4-5). Wright State jumped out to a 14-2 lead in the first eight minutes and led by as many as 14 points on the way to a 34-23 halftime score. The Penguins pulled within 7 points on two free throws by Roberts with 6:10 left, but a 3-pointer by Vaughn Duggins and jumper by Wood put it out of reach, and the Raiders made three more foul shots down the stretch. Duggins finished with nine points. Wright State scored 19 points off turnovers, to six for the Penguins.
